@startuml
' --- whole-map provenance: cycle that introduced each @id ---
' @cycle(SEQ-ARCH-DIFF, 0029)
' @id(SEQ-ARCH-DIFF)
' @ref(USE-TRACK-ARCH)
' @desc(SEQ-ARCH-DIFF, "Implemented as Project::arch_diff + Project::arch_status (crates/mdd-core/src/lib.rs) over the architecture.rs engine. diff: load_architecture parses the working .mdd/architecture/*.yml, read_text_at_ref reads the base via `git show <ref>:<path>` (default HEAD; absent = empty), then architecture::diff. status: load + architecture::check vs the model registry ids, exit non-zero on any violation. The same check() is folded into Project::validate_inner as WARNING-level OCL-ARCH-* rules (inert when no spec). CLI: mdd-cli Commands::Arch (diff/status, --json).")
' Current-side sequence for mdd arch diff / status (cycle 0029).
title mdd arch diff and status (current)

actor "Developer / Agent" as Agent
participant "mdd arch (CLI)" as CLI
participant "Project::load_architecture" as Load
participant "git show ref" as Git
participant "architecture::diff / check" as Core

alt mdd arch diff
  Agent -> CLI : mdd arch diff [--base ref]
  CLI -> Load : parse working .mdd/architecture
  CLI -> Git : read .mdd/architecture at base ref
  Git --> CLI : base spec (empty if absent)
  CLI -> Core : diff(base, head)
  Core --> CLI : ArchDiff (added / removed / changed)
else mdd arch status
  Agent -> CLI : mdd arch status
  CLI -> Load : parse working .mdd/architecture
  CLI -> Core : check(spec, model ids)
  Core --> CLI : violations (non-zero exit if any)
end
CLI --> Agent : report (text or --json)
@enduml
